        (4499, 'Tom Shadyac', '1958-12-11', 'Thomas Peter "Tom" Shadyac is an American comedian, director, screenwriter, and producer. Although Shadyac had been the youngest joke-writer ever for comedian Bob Hope,[1] he is widely known for writing and directing the films Ace Ventura: Pet Detective, The Nutty Professor, Liar Liar, Bruce Almighty, and I Am. He is an adjunct professor of communication and teaches screenwriting at Pepperdine University''s Seaver College.', 'Falls Church, Virginia, USA', 1, '/8CtwYIVmCSDQ9F1SXFpifKW0N3v.jpg'),
