        (5168, 'Gabriel Byrne', '1950-05-12', 'An Irish actor, film director, film producer, writer, cultural ambassador and audiobook narrator. His acting career began in the Focus Theatre before he joined London’s Royal Court Theatre in 1979. Byrne''s screen début came in the Irish soap opera The Riordans and the spin-off show Bracken. The actor has now starred in over 35 feature films, such as The Usual Suspects, Miller''s Crossing and Stigmata, in addition to writing two. Byrne''s producing credits include the Academy Award-nominated In the Name of the Father. Currently, he is receiving much critical acclaim for his role as Dr. Paul Weston in the HBO drama In Treatment.', 'Dublin, Ireland', 2, '/yQR6Exu12940oRXoCWmwULyWLP8.jpg'),
        (5169, 'J.E. Freeman', '1946-02-02', 'J.E. Freeman (born February 2, 1946) is an American actor, often cast in tough guy roles. His first movie appearance was in the early 80''s actionner An Eye for an Eye in which he plays a tow truck driver who minces words with Chuck Norris.

He is especially known for his menacing characters roles : the evil gangster Marcelles Santos in David Lynch''s Wild at Heart, the terrifying Eddie Dane, ferocious gay hitman from Miller''s Crossing, and the infamous scientist Mason Wren in Alien Resurrection. Other notable apparitions in : Ruthless People, Patriot Games, Copycat and Go.

