        (5313, 'Lena Olin', '1955-03-22', 'From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Lena Maria Jonna Olin (born 22 March 1955) is a Swedish actress. She has been nominated for several acting awards, including a Golden Globe for The Unbearable Lightness of Being (1988) and an Academy Award for Enemies, A Love Story (1989). Other well-known films in which she has appeared include Chocolat (2000), directed by her husband Lasse Hallström, Queen of the Damned (2002), Casanova (2005) and The Reader (2008). Olin was also a main cast member in the second season (and a recurring guest star in later seasons) of the television series Alias. Olin starred in the Swedish sitcom Welcome to Sweden.', 'Stockholm, Stockholms län, Sweden', 3, '/cmekM6MgihkMoFZ1ZNAoSMbcjv4.jpg'),
