        (7167, 'Don Rickles', '1926-05-08', 'Don Rickles, nicknamed "Mr. Warmth", was an American stand-up comedian and actor. He acted in comedic and dramatic roles, but is best known as an insult comic. He enjoyed a sustained career as such, thanks to his distinctive humor, wit, and impeccable timing. Rickles frequently appeared as a guest on The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson.', 'Queens, New York, U.S.', 1, '/h5BcaDMPRVLHLDzbQavec4xfSdt.jpg'),
